          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I'll be honest: when I first heard about an AI platform built specifically for Christian content teams, I raised an eyebrow. Most AI tools feel generic—templated, soulless, and disconnected from anything resembling ministry work. Then I tried ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ", and everything shifted.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This isn't another ChatGPT wrapper dressed up for churches. Dry Ground AI understands the rhythms of ministry life: the Sunday deadline that never moves, the devotional series that needs consistency, the outreach email that has to land with care. It was built for teams who carry the weight of communicating hope every single week.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://partners.dryground.ai/vqh9n364qwmn"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here are seven real-world use cases that show why ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI is worth exploring",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " for any ministry-driven organization.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
