        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Sermon Series Development from Scratch",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Preparing a six-week sermon series used to take me 20+ hours of research, outlining, and drafting. With Dry Ground AI, I can input a theme—say, \"Faith in Uncertain Times\"—and receive a structured series outline complete with scripture references, illustrative stories, and application points for each week.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The tool doesn't replace the pastor's voice. It accelerates the research and scaffolding phase. One youth pastor I spoke with used it to build a Romans study series in under three hours. He still rewrote every sermon in his own words, but the heavy lifting of cross-referencing commentaries and organizing themes? Done.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "> *Disclosure: This post contains affiliate links. I may earn a commission if you subscribe through my links, at no extra cost to you.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://partners.dryground.ai/vqh9n364qwmn"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you've ever stared at a blank page on Wednesday night with Sunday looming, ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "this kind of head start",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " changes the game.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Daily Devotional Content at Scale",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Churches and ministries that publish daily devotionals face a brutal content treadmill. Five devotions per week, 52 weeks per year—that's 260 pieces of content annually. Most small teams can't sustain that pace without burnout or inconsistency.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI generates devotional drafts with scripture passages, reflection questions, and practical takeaways. A communications director at a mid-size church in Texas told me she uses it to produce a month's worth of devotionals in a single afternoon. She edits for tone and theological nuance, but the skeleton is always solid.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-dry-ground-ai"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Want to see exactly how this workflow looks? Check out our ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "step-by-step tutorial on using Dry Ground AI",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Outreach Emails and Newsletter Campaigns",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Most church communication teams aren't staffed with copywriters. They're volunteers or staff members juggling five other roles. Writing an Easter outreach email, a year-end giving campaign, or a community event invitation often gets pushed to the bottom of the list.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI handles this beautifully. You describe the audience, the event, and the tone you want—warm and inviting, urgent and compassionate, celebratory—and it drafts emails that actually sound like a person wrote them. Not a robot. Not a marketer. A real human who cares.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I tested it with a Christmas Eve invitation campaign. The drafts needed minimal editing: a tweak to the service times, a swap of one illustration, and they were ready to send. That kind of speed matters when your team is already stretched thin.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-dry-ground-ai"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "See how Dry Ground AI handles ministry communication",
            "marks": [
              "l4"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
