      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. Small Group Study Guides",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Creating discussion guides for small groups is tedious but essential ministry work. You need thoughtful questions tied to scripture, application prompts that spark real conversation, and a format that works for both in-person and online settings.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI generates study guides that follow a clear arc: observation questions (what does the text say?), interpretation questions (what does it mean?), and application questions (how do we live it out?). Group leaders I've talked to say the guides feel pastorally sensitive, not academic or sterile.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "One campus ministry leader uses it weekly to produce guides for her 15 small groups. Before Dry Ground AI, she was spending her entire Friday on this task. Now it takes 45 minutes.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. Social Media Content for Ministry Accounts",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Running a church's Instagram or Facebook page is deceptively time-consuming. You need scripture graphics with captions, event announcements, encouraging midweek posts, and stories that reflect your community's personality.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l5",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-gamma"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI can generate caption copy, suggest hashtag strategies, and even draft short video scripts for Reels or YouTube Shorts. It won't design your graphics—that's where tools like ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Gamma",
            "marks": [
              "l5"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " come in—but for the words? It delivers consistently.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A worship leader in Florida told me she batches a full month of social captions in 90 minutes now. Her engagement went up 40% because she could finally post consistently instead of in sporadic bursts.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
