          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Not at all. While pastors benefit from sermon prep support, the tool is equally valuable for church communications directors, volunteer teams, ministry coordinators, worship leaders, and Christian nonprofit staff. Anyone responsible for producing faith-based content will find practical value in it.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How is Dry Ground AI different from using ChatGPT for ministry content?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dry Ground AI is purpose-built for Christian ministry workflows. It understands theological traditions, provides proper scripture integration with cross-references, supports team collaboration, and offers content calendar planning. Generic AI tools require extensive prompting and often produce output that feels generic or theologically off-base. Dry Ground AI starts from a place of ministry understanding.",
